Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue State on Saturday sent a heart-felt congratulatory message to former President Olusegun Obasanjo on his 85th birthday anniversary. Governor Ortom in a statement by his chief press secretary, Nathaniel Ikyur, emphasized that Dr. Obasanjo has “remained an epitome of greatness, an accomplished and foremost political leader here in Nigeria and globally for all seasons.”
Governor Ortom thanked Obasanjo “for continually making strong impacts and interventions in numerous political issues in our dear country and elsewhere;” saying, “This has no doubt built confidence among fellow countrymen and nations.”
Governor Ortom expressed that Dr. Obasanjo’s “historic accomplishments as Nigeria’s President on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) are legendary.”
The Benue governor highlighted: “Under your Presidency, you stabilised Nigeria’s democracy, depoliticised the military, restored Nigeria’s global reputation and leadership.
“You also reformed the banking sector, cleared our debts, revolutionised the telecommunication industry just as you successfully privatised moribund public enterprises and institutionalised the fight against corruption.
“To keep the country in peace, you safeguarded the lives and properties of this great African nation. Above all, you strengthened the bond of Nigeria’s unity.”
Ortom maintained that till date, former President Obasanjo has remained Nigeria’s most accomplished statesman” who has verified track records of achievements both nationally and internationally.
Ortom wished Obasanjo good health, divine protection, and a longer life.
 
 
